# Copy this file to .env and fill in your own values.
# .env is gitignored and must never be committed.

# Google Maps API key for Android native map tiles (react-native-maps).
# Required for map views to load on Android (PROVIDER_GOOGLE is used).
# On iOS, Apple Maps (MapKit) is used instead — no key needed.
# On web, maps are not shown at all.
#
# How to create a key:
#   1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
#   2. Enable the "Maps SDK for Android" API.
#   3. Create an API key and restrict it to your app's package name
#      (com.sassagold.roamly) and its SHA-1 signing certificate.
#   4. For EAS cloud builds, also add this key as an EAS secret:
#      npx eas secret:create --scope project --name GOOGLE_MAPS_ANDROID_API_KEY
GOOGLE_MAPS_ANDROID_API_KEY=
